-- Bernhard won't join Chrysler management: Cerberus
-- 
-- Mon May 14, 2007 5:46pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/14/us-daimlerchrysler-cerberus-bernhard-idUSWEA282020070514

 

 STUTTGART, Germany  (Reuters) - Former Chrysler chief operating officer Wolfgang Bernhard will not take an active role in helping to restructure the loss-making Chrysler Group once again, Cerberus Capital Management CBS.UL said on Monday. 

 "He will not join the management team at Chrysler," Chairman John Snow told a news conference. Bernhard had advised Cerberus on its purchase of a majority stake in Chrysler. Bernhard, a highly respected manager within the industry, ran the Volkswagen Brand Group until the end of January.